
[1]pigeon

   PIG'EON, n. A fowl of the genus Columba, of several species, as the
   stock dove, the ring dove, the turtle dove, and the migratory or wild
   pigeon of America. The domestic pigeon breeds in a box, often attached
   to a building, called a dovecot or pigeon-house. The wild pigeon builds
   a nest on a tree in the forest.
